quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  2,72,"Then, when you [Israelites] killed someone and started to blame one another, God brought to light what you concealed"
  2,73,"We said, \"Strike [the corpse] with a part of it.\" Thus God restores the dead to life and shows you His signs, so that you may understand"
  2,74,"Then your hearts became as hard as rock or even harder: for, there are rocks from which streams gush forth; and, there are some that cleave asunder and water flows out from them, while others fall down for fear of God. God is not unaware of what you do"
  2,75,"Do you then hope that they will believe in you when some of them have already heard the word of God and then, after having understood it, they knowingly perverted it"
  2,76,"When they meet the faithful, they say, \"We are believers.\" But when alone, they say to each other, \"Must you tell them what God has revealed to us? They will only use it to argue against you before your Lord! Have you no sense"
  2,77,Do they not know that God knows all that they conceal and all that they disclose
  2,78,"There are among them unlettered people who have no real knowledge of the Scriptures, knowing only their own wishful thinking and following only conjecture"
  2,79,"Woe to those who write the scripture with their own hands, and then declare, \"This is from God,\" in order to sell it for a paltry price. Woe to them because of what their own hands have written, and woe to them for what they have earned"
  2,80,"They say, \"The Fire is not going to touch us, and [even if it does], it will only be for a few days!\" Say [to them], \"Have you received a promise from God, for God never breaks His promise, or do you attribute something to God which you do not know"
  2,81,"Truly, those who do evil and are encompassed by their misdeeds, shall be the inmates of the Fire. Therein they shall abide forever"
  2,82,but those who believe and do good works are the heirs of Paradise; there they shall abide forever